# Decade Exchange Monorepo Conventions

- Packages live in `packages/<name>/`, published as `@decade/<name>`
- TypeScript by default; named exports, explicit return types on public functions
- Cross-package imports use package names, not relative paths
- Money is integer **cents** (`Cents`) everywhere — never floats
- Files under ~300 lines; no `any` without justification
- Shared configs (tsconfig, eslint, prettier) live at the repo root
- Build tool: tsup (ESM + DTS). Test runner: Vitest
- Internal libs use `.js` import specifiers; `@decade/ui` (transpiled by Next, not
  built) uses extensionless imports
- See `UBIQUITOUS_LANGUAGE.md` for canonical domain terms

## Packages

`typescript-config`, `eslint-config`, `types`, `logger`, `matching-engine`, `db`,
`auth`, `ui`, `exchange-runtime`, `mcp` (+ `apps/web`).
